NASSAU, Bahamas (AP) -- Hurricane Floyd strengthened to a very   dangerous Category 4 storm today with 155 mph wind, surprising  forecasters and charging toward the Bahamas on a path that also  threatened the Florida coast.
MIAMI (AP) -- Authorities urged nearly 2 million people to   evacuate coastal areas stretching from Florida to North Carolina  today as Hurricane Floyd, one of the most powerful and biggest  storms to ever threaten the United States, roared through the  Bahamas.
